# Starknet Agent Project Instructions

## Overview
- Starknet Agent is an AI-powered search engine specifically designed for the Starknet Ecosystem.
- It uses Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) to provide accurate, source-cited answers to questions about Starknet and Cairo.
- The project is built with TypeScript, Node.js, Express, MongoDB, and Next.js.

## Architecture
- Monorepo structure with multiple packages:
  - `packages/agents/`: Core RAG agent implementation
  - `packages/backend/`: Express server with WebSocket support
  - `packages/ui/`: Next.js frontend application
  - `packages/ingester/`: Data ingestion tools
  - `packages/typescript-config/`: Shared TypeScript configuration

## Key Features
- RAG-based search across multiple Starknet resources
- Real-time streaming of responses
- Multiple focus modes for specific resources
- Source citations for all answers
- Chat history for context in follow-up questions

## Development Workflow
- Use `turbo dev` to start the development server
- MongoDB Atlas is used for vector database storage
- Configuration is managed through TOML files
- Docker is used for containerization and deployment

## AI Guidance
- Focus on the RAG pipeline in `packages/agents/src/pipeline/` for agent-related queries
- Use `packages/backend/src/websocket/` for understanding real-time communication
- Refer to `packages/ui/components/` for UI-related questions
- Check `packages/ingester/scripts/` for data ingestion processes

## Testing
- Jest is used for testing
- Run tests with `turbo test`
- Test files are located in `__tests__/` directories

## Deployment
- Docker Compose is used for deployment
- Production configuration is in `docker-compose.prod-hosted.yml`
- Environment variables should be set according to `.env.example` files
